723797f-a.title: Manhattan: Vesey Street - Washington Street
723797f-a.text:
77-81 Vesey Street, at the S.E. corner of Washington Street, showing
only the lower stories of building concerned. Shown on the extreme right
is a portion of the Washington Market, reputed to be the largest wholesale
vegetable and fruit market in the world.
August 1, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
723797f-a.folder: Vesey Street & Washington Street, Manhattan, NY

723798f-b.title: Manhattan: Vesey Street - Washington Street
723798f-b.text:
(1)
Vesey Street, north side, east from, but not including Washington
Street. The view shows the new Post Office in process of construction.
Towering over all is the Woolworth Building.
August 31, 199S.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same; another view.
August 31, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
The same, at an earlier date, showing clearance;on the site where
steel constructhon is in progress on the United States Post Office
Building. The building to the right of the Woolworth, is the 44-story
Transportation Building at the S.W. corner of Barclay Street and
Broadway.
April 3, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
